.el .ds Aq '
.TH btctax-reconcile-promote-tranche 1  btctax "btctax manual"
.SH NAME
promote\-tranche \- Approach\-B: promote an already\-declared `DeclareTranche` (D\-8\*(Aqs $0 IRS fallback) to a filed `>$0` basis floor (the minimum daily closing price over the attested acquisition window), behind a mandatory purchase\-provenance attestation (BG\-D5), a two\-sided informed\-consent screen (BG\-D6), and a Form 8275 Part II narrative (BG\-D7). Mitigates penalty exposure; does not eliminate it or guarantee immunity — read the consent screen this verb prints before acknowledging
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpromote\-tranche\fR <\fB\-\-provenance\fR> <\fB\-\-part\-ii\-file\fR> [\fB\-\-i\-acknowledge\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fITARGET\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Approach\-B: promote an already\-declared `DeclareTranche` (D\-8\*(Aqs $0 IRS fallback) to a filed `>$0` basis floor (the minimum daily closing price over the attested acquisition window), behind a mandatory purchase\-provenance attestation (BG\-D5), a two\-sided informed\-consent screen (BG\-D6), and a Form 8275 Part II narrative (BG\-D7). Mitigates penalty exposure; does not eliminate it or guarantee immunity — read the consent screen this verb prints before acknowledging
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-provenance\fR \fI<PROVENANCE>\fR
The units\*(Aq real acquisition provenance. Promotion requires `purchase`; every other value is refused and pointed at modeling the real acquisition instead (BG\-D5)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
purchase
.IP \(bu 2
gift
.IP \(bu 2
inheritance
.IP \(bu 2
mining
.IP \(bu 2
earned
.IP \(bu 2
airdrop
.IP \(bu 2
fork
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-part\-ii\-file\fR \fI<PART_II_FILE>\fR
Path to a text file holding the Form 8275 Part II narrative (filer facts, Reg. §1.6662\-4(f), "in sufficient detail"). An empty or whitespace\-only file is refused at record time (BG\-D7)
.TP
\fB\-\-i\-acknowledge\fR \fI<I_ACKNOWLEDGE>\fR
Non\-interactive consent: the exact acknowledgment phrase shown on the consent screen. On an interactive terminal, omitting this shows the screen and prompts for the phrase
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fITARGET\fR>
The `DeclareTranche` decision to promote (see `btctax events list` for the ref)
